8// Normally we wouldn't really need the *entire* table, but upgrades are a little different.
9// Given they use full scans, any entry can unintentionally change behaviour.
10// As such, we should use our entire table here to be safe.
11
12// Generated from the following:
13/*
14 SELECT
15 CONCAT('{ .Index = ', nIndex,
16 ', .OriginType = ', nOriginType,
17 ', .OriginItem = ', nOriginItem,
18 ', .RequiredItem = { ', nReqItem1, ', ', nReqItem2, ' }',
19 ', .RequiredCoins = ', nReqNoah,
20 ', .RateType = ', bRateType,
21 ', .GenRate = ', nGenRate,
22 ', .GiveItem = ', nGiveitem,
23 ' }, ')
24 FROM ITEM_UPGRADE
25 ORDER BY nIndex ASC
26*/
27
